  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Need more parking machines&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I took my daughter to urgent care this morning. Overall satisfied with the service, however the doctor who saw my daughter was stood at reception for 20 minutes talking to the receptionist team. 

After treatment I asked where the nearest car park machine was and I was advised to the right of the main entrance. I walked to this machine but it was out of order and had a sign advising to pay at the machine at ATC.  I have a blue badge as I have problems with both my knees and walking is very painful. I walked over to the ATC and the doors were locked. I had to walk back to the main entrance and all round the hospital and back to pay causing me significant pain

I understand the cost implications of putting more machines in but obviously the people who have decided where to put these machines don’t have mobility problems and are not unwell. I also think that the parking is very expensive. I regularly use hospitals in other health authorities for specialist services and there charges are 20 mins free and then it’s &amp;amp;#163;1 per hour.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
